sql:
SELECT preferred_industries
FROM user_preferences
WHERE user_id = 0;

SELECT correlation_coefficient, date
FROM correlations
WHERE stock_id_1 = 5 AND stock_id_2 = 7 AND date = '2023-10-01';

SELECT ticker, market_cap
FROM stocks
WHERE ticker IN (SELECT preferred_stocks FROM user_preferences WHERE user_id = 0);

SELECT AVG(s.market_cap) AS avg_market_cap
FROM stocks s
WHERE s.ticker IN (SELECT preferred_stocks FROM user_preferences WHERE user_id = 0);

external_knowledge:
Sector 7 may refer to the Technology sector, which includes companies that primarily deal with technology such as computer hardware, software, and networking equipment; 
The country 'USA' refers to the United States of America;
Average correlation coefficient represents the strength and direction of the linear relationship between two stocks' price movements, with 1 indicating a perfect positive correlation, -1 indicating a perfect negative correlation, and 0 indicating no linear correlation.
